Class R2DResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.receiver2d.engine.io.R2DResource
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WorldResource

    public class R2DResource
extends Object
    Useful for loading scene resources dynamically from the local filesystem.

    • Method Detail

      • setResource

        public boolean setResource(String loc,
                           String type)
        Changes the current resource to a different one.
        Parameters:
        loc - The location (in the filesystem) of the resource.
        type - The mime-type of the resource.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the operation was successful in changing the resource. This is affected by whether or not the file exists in the system. If not, the resource remains unchanged.

      • setResource

        public boolean setResource(String loc)
        Changes the current resource to a different one.
        Parameters:
        loc - The location (in the filesystem) of the resource.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the operation was successful in changing the resource. This is affected by whether or not the file exists in the system. If not, the resource remains unchanged.

      • load

        public boolean load()
        Loads a file into memory from the resource's current path. This must be called before calling getLoaded().
        Returns:
        true if the operation was successful, false if otherwise

      • unload

        public void unload()
        Clears the file from memory by setting it to null. Does not remove the location variable of the resource, though.

      • getFile

        public File getFile()
        Gets the loaded file from the resource's location, or null if undefined. If the file is not loaded prior by calling .load() then it is loaded automatically.
        Returns:
        The file of the loaded resource.

      • getPath

      • getInputStream

        public FileInputStream getInputStream()
        Gets the input stream of the currently loaded resource.
        Returns:
        The input stream, or null if the file is not loaded.
